==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Cyprus
<hw>Cy"prus</hw> <pr>(s?"pr?s)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[OE.
<ets>cipres</ets>, <ets>cypirs</ets>; perh. so named as being first
manufactured in Cyprus. Cf. <er>Cipers</er>.]</ety> <def>A thin,
transparent stuff, the same as, or corresponding to, crape. It was
either white or black, the latter being most common, and used for
mourning.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Lawn as white as driven snow,⟦br⟧
<qex>Cyprus</qex> black as e'er was crow.</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Cypruslawn</ent>⟦br⟧
